===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[image]], [[symbol]], [[picture]], or other [[representation]] usually as an object of religious devotion.
#: {{syn|en|idol|graven image|q2=pejorative}}
# {{lb|en|religion|especially|Eastern Christianity}} A type of religious painting portraying a [[saint]] or scene from [[Scripture]], often done on wooden panels.
#* {{quote-journal|en|title=‘Weeping Virgin’ Icon Draws Throngs To Chicago|work=The New York Times|date=1986-12-22|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1986/12/22/us/weeping-virgin-icon-draws-throngs-to-chicago.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=Last week the Archdiocese sent emmissaries to investigate the '''icon''' and decided that the tears were not a hoax, Father Koufos said.}}
# {{lb|en|by extension}} A person or thing that is the best example of a certain profession or some doing.
#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:exemplar|Thesaurus:model}}
#: {{ux|en|That man is an '''icon''' in the business; he personifies loyalty and good business sense.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Robert Palmer|title=Two Icons of Rock Music|work=The New York Times|date=1981-05-31|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1981/05/31/arts/two-icons-of-rock-music.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=Only a handful of rock musicians have become genuine '''icons''' - larger-than-life symbolic figures whose personal triumphs and vicissitudes seem to mirror the ups and downs of rock as a whole, and sometimes of the society that nurtures it. Often, rock '''icons''' become the objects of personality cults that tend to overshadow their musical accomplishments.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|title=Barbie: Doll, Icon Or Sexist Symbol?|work=The New York Times|date=1987-12-23|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/12/23/garden/barbie-doll-icon-or-sexist-symbol.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=Barbie is viewed as an '''icon''' of American culture in her new biography, ''Barbie: Her Life and Times'' (Crown, $25), written by Billy Boy, a clothing and jewelry designer in Paris.}}
# {{lb|en|graphical user interface}} A small picture that represents something.
#: {{ux|en|Click the loudspeaker '''icon''' to configure audio settings.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Erik Snadberg-Diment|title=Number Crunching on the Macintosh|work=The New York Times|date=1985-09-15|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1985/09/15/business/the-executive-computer-number-crunching-on-the-macintosh.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=The program's most quintessentially Macintoshian feature, one as yet unique among spreadsheets, is its '''icon''' bar, which resides at the top of the screen just below the standard menu bar. It contains 21 '''icons''', each of which allows the user to perform a specified function with but a few clicks of the mouse.}}
# {{lb|en|linguistics|semiotics}} A word, character, or sign whose form reflects and is determined by the [[referent]]; [[onomatopoeic]] words are necessarily all icons.
#: {{cot|en|symbol|index}}.

